    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm not sure i follow. you said accountability \"shouldn't be conflated with silencing dissent,\" but most people who feel silenced would say that's exactly what's happening. if a certain viewpoint gets deplatformed or labeled as \"harmful\" to the point where people are afraid to say it, isn't that just censorship by another name? it feels like you're trying to redefine censorship as something positive.",
